<font color="#FF0000">BUG ON THE WINDSHIELD</font><br>
<tt>Fri Aug 22  1:22:27 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Any landing that you can walk away from is a good Landing!<br><br>
Crash landed at the VA Hospital over in Kansas.<br>
Had my Jesus Nut retorqued.<br>
Lost a lot of good pals in August and September 1966.<br>
My feet still are giving up little pieces of plexiglass..some scaring... tiny metal particals long since dissolved.  Need a good VA blacksmith so I can trudge the woods when Autumn gets here.<br>
Had some severe thunderstorms lately... should dry out enough to resume hay baling tomorrow.<br>
VA is going to give me some new eyeglasses next month.<br>
Got my little girl, Rachael back...after an eleven year battle.  I've had custody since the end of May.  I bought her a mountain bike for her 13th birthday which occurs on August 29th.  She's good with a black powder rifle... started the 8th grade a couple of weeks ago... wants to play basketball.  She drives my truck in the pastures and on the back roads... thinks she is hot stuff.  She loves me.  Hope I can be a good Daddy.  She sure is a pretty little half breed Comanche.<br>
Had some good fried chicken on the way home.<br>
Trying hard not to think about some things that don't need thinking about.<br>
Thanks for what all of you did a long time ago.  Thanks for the kind words and for &quot;Being There!&quot;<br>
The Doc told me that my arrogance had a good chance for recovery.<br><br>
Best to you and yours<br><br>
Mustang Two Four... laying on the hangar floor.
